The article discusses conversations between US officials and United Nations (UN) representatives regarding the recent terrorist attack by Hamas on Israel and the humanitarian situation in Gaza. National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and UN Secretary-General Antonio Guterres discussed the attack on October 12. On October 13, Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer, along with UN Special Coordinator for the Middle East Peace Process Tor Wennesland and USAID Administrator Samantha Power, discussed the challenging humanitarian conditions in Gaza. They also talked about efforts to ensure safe movement for civilians seeking protection in Gaza and facilitate humanitarian access, including providing water, food, and medical care.